# Skill Operating System (Phase 22)

Read **[SKILLOS.md](../../SKILLOS.md)** before changes to skill persistence, permissions, health, or rollout.

## Layer ownership (mandatory before implementation)

| Surface | Owner |
|---------|-------|
| Skill definitions, versions, global governance | **Platform Admin** |
| Installed skills, permissions, learning preferences | **Customer App** |
| Execution, health reporting, permission validation | **Install Engine** |

## Rules

1. Every Skill must register in `lib/core/skills/registry.ts` **and** persist via SkillOS tables when runtime state is needed
2. Least privilege — Skills request only required permissions; new permissions require customer approval
3. Learning default is **assisted** — modes: `disabled`, `assisted`, `adaptive`
4. No public marketplace UI until explicitly approved — database prep only
5. Release pipeline: Aipify Internal → Unonight Pilot → Beta Customers → Stable Release
6. Success score range 0–100 via `compute_skill_success_score()`
7. Phase 16 code registry and Phase 22 DB state are complementary — do not duplicate definitions without sync plan
8. Install health via `POST /api/install/skill-health` only — no cross-tenant DB access
9. Skill events and audit logs must never store email content, chat, orders, or PII

> A coordinated team of specialised Skills — not one AI trying to do everything.
